title: For Sale:  Rossi Coach Gun, External Hammers, 20ga
postcontent:
SOLD

Here is a Rossi 20 Gauge Coach Gun. It has 20" barrels, has the original Rossi butt plate. It is an older model with an S-prefix, 5-digit serial number, and the cross-bolt design. It is the same as the Overland model, but it was made before they were named Overland. Unfortunately, it was stored poorly and has rust and pitting on the external surfaces. However, the bore is perfect and I don't think I've seen a nicer one. The pitting is on the right barrel near the muzzle, the bottom between the two barrels, and on the barrel rib near the muzzle. There is also light pitting on the left side of the receiver, and a scratch on the left side of the butt stock.

The gun is nice and tight. The 20 gauge Rossis are especially nice because the frame of the gun is actually sized for a 20 gauge instead of just having 20 gauge barrels mounted on a 12 gauge frame. This is a really nice gun.

These Rossi shotguns are great because they are solid and reliable, and there are no extra safeties like the unnecessary tang safety that you find on currently manufactured hammered shotguns.

More photos available, just ask.

Price is $300.00, plus $30 for shipping and insurance.

The finish on this rifle is completely original and there's quite a bit of it! The receiver retains about 80% finish with some handling marks and a touch of light corrosion along the upper left edge. The barrel and magazine tube retain even more finish and rate 92-94% overall. There are some handling marks and one ding to the side of the barrel on the right side. The rear barrel sight has been removed and a period Lyman No.1 combination tang sight (correctly coded "DA") installed. Judging from the finish on the tang and lack of sight elevator wear on the barrel, this tang sight has been installed for a long while, probably since the rifle was new. The rear sight dovetail is filled with lead. Some case colors are still visible on the more protected surfaces of the lever. The stocks are in very good condition with handling wear, some dents and scratches. There are no cracks or chips and quite a bit of original varnish is still visible on the butt. The butt-stock displays exceptional figure, particularly on the left side. The rifle is in excellent mechanical condition...the takedown is nice and snug and the action is crisp. The bore is very good, near excellent with strong, sharp rifling that is lightly frosted but without any pits.A neat old Winchester in far above average condition!
California Residents: We do ship to California whenever legal to do so.
